text: Dahigaon Korhale is a village in Rahata taluka of Ahmednagar district in the Indian state of Maharashtra. It is located near Rahata city. ==Population== As per 2011 census, population of village is 2077, of which 1096 are males and 981 are females. ==Transport== ===Road=== Dahigaon Korhale is connected to nearby villages by village roads. Ahmednagar-Manmad State highway passes near from village. ===Rail=== Shirdi Railway Station is nearest railway station to a village. ===Air=== Shirdi Airport is located at distance of 9km from a village. ==See also== *List of villages in Rahata taluka == References == Category:Villages in Ahmednagar district
title: Dahigaon Korhale
